sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K392045
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: endoglucanase secretion testing construct for yeast
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Yeast expression device containing C. fermi endoglucanase CenA with engineered secretion tag attached upstream to enable secretion.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tadashi Nakamura, Shuhei Yasumoto, Saya Kakuda, Takahiro Saka
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Silver assembly of J63005, K416003, K392006, K392003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Assembled from Silver standard-compatible parts. Sequence shown on part's main page may not be accurate since it assumes Standard assembly. Please check sequencing results from Get This Part page instead.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: P0310
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caroline Ajo-Franklin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: genomic DNA of ADH1 from S. cerevisiae

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K416003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This secretion tag when linked to the N-terminal of the protein directs extracellular secretion of the protein. After targeting through the ER to the golgi, this "pre-pro" tag is cleaved by the KEX-2 protease resulting in secretion of protein without the aforementioned tag. To use this tag, attached it directly upstream of your proteins CDS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Phair
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was sent to use from Dr. Sheldon Park of the University of Buffalo.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There was an illegal Xbal1 site at bp 101 and we removed it through altering the primers necessary for biobricking the sequence.
